quran[7]{c,v,t,f}:
  95,1,"By the fig and the olive;"{1},footnotes:1:1
  95,2,"and by the Mount Sinai,"{1},footnotes:1:1
  95,3,"and by this city (of Makkah), a haven of peace:"
  95,4,"surely We created man in the best mould;"{1},footnotes:1:1
  95,5,"then We reverted him to the lowest of the low,"{1},footnotes:1:1
  95,6,"except those who have faith and do righteous deeds. Theirs is a never ending reward."{1},footnotes:1:1
  95,7,"Who, then, can give the lie to you, (O Prophet), about the Reward and the Punishment?"{1},footnotes:1:1
  95,8,"Is not Allah the Greatest of all sovereigns?"{1},footnotes:1:1
  96,1,"Recite in the name of your Lord Who created,"{1}{2}{3},footnotes:1:1,footnotes:2:2,footnotes:3:3
  96,2,"created man from a clot of congealed blood."{1},footnotes:1:1
  96,3,"Recite: and your Lord is Most Generous,"
  96,4,"Who taught by the pen,"{1},footnotes:1:1
  96,5,"taught man what he did not know."{1},footnotes:1:1
  96,6,"Nay, surely man transgresses;"{1},footnotes:1:1
  96,7,"for he believes himself to be self-sufficient."{1},footnotes:1:1
  96,8,"Surely to your Lord is your return."{1},footnotes:1:1
  96,9,"Did you see him who forbids"
  96,10,"a servant (of Allah) when he prays?"{1},footnotes:1:1